**Following OP comment about sizing of elements**

I notice that you don&#39;t specifically mention that you are using `border-box` as your `box-sizing` methods.  I have added this into the snippet now.

Using `border-box` means that when you specify the size of a box, you are including the borders inside that size.

For example, if the width is set to 100%, this is 100% _including_ any borders you have on your elements.  Most normalized stylesheets set `box-sizing` to `border-box` by default.

